Parliament, Monday, 2 September 2019 – The Select Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs will tomorrow, 03 September 2019, visit Msunduzi and Mtubatuba Local Municipality in KwaZulu-Natal to do an In-Loco oversight visit as required by the constitution, following the invocation of Section 139 (1)(b) of the Constitution. The committee will be divided into two groups in order to cover the two municipalities. The visit follows a decision taken by the KwaZulu Natal provincial executive to intervene in the municipalities as per Section 139 (1)(b) of the Constitution. This decision followed various challenges impacting negatively on service delivery within the municipalities. The National Council of Provinces is mandated by Section 139 (2)(c) to, review the intervention regularly and may make any appropriate recommendation to the provincial executive while the intervention continues. This oversight visit is in keeping with this directive. The committee will use the visit to interact with stakeholders including the MEC responsible for Cooperative Governance, Councillors and Ward Committees, organised labour and other forums. Details of the Visit (Group 1) Date: 03 September 2019
	Venue: Msunduzi Local Municipality offices, Pietermaritzburg
	Time: 9:00 Details of the Visit (Group 2) Date: 03 September 2019
	Venue: Mtubatuba Local Municipality offices, Mtubatuba
	Time: 9:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON COOPERATIVE GOVERNANCE AND TRADITIONAL AFFAIRS For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
